reviews.review_text: Sound 5 : Show 3.5 Wow.  The sound quality is stunning.  A twenty-five year old cassette master?  Great mix, great presence and levels, nice warm analog sound (even though it was re-mastered digitally) and a damn fine show to boot.  The Sugaree opener is worth the price of admission.  Goes to show there are lots of mighty fine surprises yet to come...

Dancing Polar Bears? Thanks, archive.org for having this show around. I've been looking for a clean copy of it for a long time. I had a gawd knows what generation tape of it for years. I'll be turning on a couple of pals to this. They now live in Anchorage. And, "yes", it was the only time the Dead have ever played Alaska. I mean, consider the logistics of it. Pyramids be damned, it's COLD up there. Well, not in June...

p.s., Thanks Gans!

-NWR

nice shows the dead in alaska. as far as i know this three night run is their only trip up there. its fun to listen to because its such a unique place. this is one of those shows you should definitely listen to.....the otehr two nights get a 4 and a half to me (though i gave em a 5).....this night is a 5 hands down. best sound quality is this one.
Great Stuff I like the Alaska reference in 'Truckin'. Gans is The Man!  I need to buy that guy a beverage.
